    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-20T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-20T21:00:00-05:00" n="509"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9550: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sokobin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-21T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 21, 1937—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 21—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>City remains quiet. A group of foreigners are agitating for a large “neutral
                    zone” in Tsingtao. Plan would naturally involve important political questions
                    and therefore this Consulate unable to conceive of practical methods for its
                    realization. Has Department any suggestions?<note n="51" xml:id="d509fn51">The
                        Department replied that the matter was being given consideration.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Admiral Shimomura, Japanese senior naval officer, informed me last night that
                    Japanese forces would absolutely make no attack on or in Tsingtao unless Chinese
                    forces move against Japanese here. The Mayor previously contended Chinese would
                    make no attack on Japanese except to resist. There has been a very considerable
                    strengthening of Chinese forces on outskirts of Tsingtao.</p>
                <p>Nearly all Japanese women and children have been evacuated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sokobin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
